From 6670707175a1f8a31482bf98afb97b62c06673f4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 09:31:09 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Hide UI a user has no permission for (nav, dashboard,
 projects, controls)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Extends the existing permission-gating so users only see what they can
actually use — nothing they lack rights for appears:

- Sidebar nav: Projects/Events/Settings links now require project.read /
  alarm.read / settings.read (previously always shown).
- /projects route is gated on project.read so direct-URL access is blocked
  too, not just the link.
- Dashboard: quick-link cards and the hero "Open Projects" button are
  filtered by permission; the Quick Access section hides entirely if none
  are available.
- Projects page: Connect/Disconnect gated on device.connect; sidebar
  create/delete of projects, locations and devices gated on project.write /
  device.write.
- Start/Stop control buttons render only for the matching action
  (device.start / device.stop, or legacy device.control); the card hides if
  the user can do neither.

Adds hasAnyPermission() to AuthContext and an anyPermission prop to <Can>
so a granular OR legacy key both satisfy a check.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01UAUAvaWvRrNTJNKK2JSUTP
